  "texts": [
    "Considering the current barriers to scaling the green bond market, Deschryver and de Mariz, (2020) propose several recommendations to unlock its potential.",
    "This paper identifies the lack of harmonized global standards, the risk of greenwashing, and the perception of higher costs as key obstacles.",
    "By addressing these issues, this study aligns with SDG 8, which promotes sustained, inclusive, and sustainable economic growth, by suggesting ways to increase the scalability and effectiveness of green bonds in financing sustainable projects.",
    "The recommendations for developing clear standards and increasing transparency in the green bond market are crucial for building investor confidence and ensuring that funds are effectively channeled toward impactful and sustainable initiatives.",
    "Finally, Yeow and Ng (2021) examine the impact of green bonds on corporate environmental and financial performance, highlighting their role in improving environmental, social, and governance (ESG) metrics."
  ],
